etric'.pre` is an *outer* measure, the supremum is a measure. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.mkMetric","kind":"def","line":423,"name":"MeasureTheory.Measure.mkMetric","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.lean#L423-L427"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.mkMetric'\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Measure</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkMetric'</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/EMetricSpace/Defs.html#EMetricSpace\">EMetricSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Constructions/BorelSpace/Basic.html#BorelSpace\">BorelSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENNReal/Basic.html#ENNReal\">ENNReal</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.Measure\">Measure</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a function `m : Set X → ℝ≥0∞`, `mkMetric' m` is the supremum of `μ r`\nover `r > 0`, where `μ r` is the maximal outer measure `μ` such that `μ s ≤ m s`\nfor all `s`. While each `μ r` is an *outer* measure, the supremum is a measure. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.mkMetric'","kind":"def","line":417,"name":"MeasureTheory.Measure.mkMetric'","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.lean#L417-L421"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.le_mkMetric\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">OuterMeasure</span>.<span class=\"name\">le_mkMetric</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/EMetricSpace/Defs.html#EMetricSpace\">EMetricSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENNReal/Basic.html#ENNReal\">ENNReal</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENNReal/Basic.html#ENNReal\">ENNReal</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">μ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/OuterMeasure/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure\">OuterMeasure</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>)</span