>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.mkMetric'.le_pre","kind":"theorem","line":266,"name":"MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.mkMetric'.le_pre","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.lean#L266-L267"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.mkMetric\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">OuterMeasure</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkMetric</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/EMetricSpace/Defs.html#EMetricSpace\">EMetricSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENNReal/Basic.html#ENNReal\">ENNReal</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENNReal/Basic.html#ENNReal\">ENNReal</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/OuterMeasure/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure\">OuterMeasure</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a function `m : ℝ≥0∞ → ℝ≥0∞` and `r > 0`, let `μ r` be the maximal outer measure such that\n`μ s ≤ m (ediam s)` whenever `ediam s < r`. Then `mkMetric m = ⨆ r > 0, μ r`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.mkMetric","kind":"def","line":257,"name":"MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.mkMetric","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.lean#L257-L260"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.mkMetric'\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">OuterMeasure</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkMetric'</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/EMetricSpace/Defs.html#EMetricSpace\">EMetricSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENNReal/Basic.html#ENNReal\">ENNReal</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/OuterMeasure/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure\">OuterMeasure</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a function `m : Set X → ℝ≥0∞`, `mkMetric' m` is the supremum of `mkMetric'.pre m r`\nover `r > 0`. Equivalently, it is the limit of `mkMetric'.pre m r` as `r` tends to zero from\nthe right. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.mkMetric'","kind":"def","line":251,"name":"MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.mkMetric'","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.lean#L251-L255"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.mkMetric'.pre\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">OuterMeasure</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkMetric'</span>.<span class=\"name\">pre</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/EMetricSpace/Defs.html#EMetricSpace\">EMetricSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENNReal/Basic.html#ENNReal\">ENNReal</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">r</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENNReal/Basic.html#ENNReal\">ENNReal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/OuterMeasure/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure\">OuterMeasure</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Auxiliary definition for `OuterMeasure.mkMetric'`: given a function on sets\n`m : Set X → ℝ≥0∞`, returns the maximal outer measure `μ` such that `μ s ≤ m s`\nfor any set `s` of diameter at most `r`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.mkMetric'.pre","kind":"def","line":245,"name":"MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.mkMetric'.pre","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.lean#L245-L249"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric.le_caratheodory\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">OuterMeasure</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsMetric</span>.<span class=\"name\">le_caratheodory</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/EMetricSpace/Defs.html#EMetricSpace\">EMetricSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">μ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/OuterMeasure/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure\">OuterMeasure</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Constructions/BorelSpace/Basic.html#BorelSpace\">BorelSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hm</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric\">IsMetric</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">inst✝</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/OuterMeasure/Caratheodory.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.caratheodory\">caratheodory</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric.le_caratheodory","kind":"theorem","line":229,"name":"MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric.le_caratheodory","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.lean#L229-L232"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric.borel_le_caratheodory\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">OuterMeasure</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsMetric</span>.<span class=\"name\">borel_le_caratheodory</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/EMetricSpace/Defs.html#EMetricSpace\">EMetricSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">μ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/OuterMeasure/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure\">OuterMeasure</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hm</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric\">IsMetric</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Constructions/BorelSpace/Basic.html#borel\">borel</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/OuterMeasure/Caratheodory.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.caratheodory\">caratheodory</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"**Carathéodory's theorem**. If `m` is a metric outer measure, then every Borel measurable set\n`t` is Carathéodory measurable: for any (not necessarily measurable) set `s` we have\n`μ (s ∩ t) + μ (s \\ t) = μ s`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric.borel_le_caratheodory","kind":"theorem","line":158,"name":"MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric.borel_le_caratheodory","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.lean#L158-L227"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric.finset_iUnion_of_pairwise_separated\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">OuterMeasure</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsMetric</span>.<span class=\"name\">finset_iUnion_of_pairwise_separated</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/EMetricSpace/Defs.html#EMetricSpace\">EMetricSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">μ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/OuterMeasure/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure\">OuterMeasure</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hm</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric\">IsMetric</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">I</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">ι</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hI</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ <span class=\"fn\">i</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">I</span>, <span class=\"fn\">∀ <span class=\"fn\">j</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">I</span>, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">i</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">j</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/MetricSeparated.html#Metric.AreSeparated\">Metric.AreSeparated</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> <span class=\"fn\">j</span>)</span></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span> <span class=\"fn\">(⋃ <span class=\"fn\">i</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">I</span>, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">s</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">∑ <span class=\"fn\">i</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">I</span>, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A metric outer measure is additive on a finite set of pairwise metric separated sets. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric.finset_iUnion_of_pairwise_separated","kind":"theorem","line":144,"name":"MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric.finset_iUnion_of_pairwise_separated","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.lean#L144-L156"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">OuterMeasure</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsMetric</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/EMetricSpace/Defs.html#EMetricSpace\">EMetricSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">μ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/OuterMeasure/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure\">OuterMeasure</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We say that an outer measure `μ` in an (e)metric space is *metric* if `μ (s ∪ t) = μ s + μ t`\nfor any two metric separated sets `s`, `t`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.html#MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric","kind":"def","line":135,"name":"MeasureTheory.OuterMeasure.IsMetric","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Hausdorff.lean#L135-L138"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.Convex.Between","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Constructions.BorelSpace.Basic","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Measure.Lebesgue.Basic","Mathlib.Topology.MetricSpace.Holder","Mathlib.Topology.MetricSpace.MetricSeparated","Mathlib.Topology.Order.AtTopBotIxx"],"instances":[{"className":"MeasureTheory.Measure.IsMulLeftInvariant","name":"MeasureTheory.instIsMulLeftInvariantHausdorffMeasureOfIsIsometricSMul","typeNames":["MeasureTheory.Measure.hausdorffMeasure"]},{"className":"MeasureTheory.Measure.IsAddLeftInvariant","name":"MeasureTheory.instIsAddLeftInvariantHausdorffMeasureOfIsIsometricVAdd","typeNames":["MeasureTheory.Measure.hausdorffMeasure"]},{"className":"MeasureTheory.Measure.IsMulRightInvariant","name":"MeasureTheory.instIsMulRightInvariantHausdorffMeasureOfIsIsometricSMulMulOpposite","typeNames":["MeasureTheory.Measure.hausdorffMeasure"]},{"className":"MeasureTheory.Measure.IsAddRightInvariant","name":"MeasureTheory.instIsAddRightInvariantHausdorffMeasureOfIsIsometricVAddAddOpposite","typeNames":["MeasureTheory.Measure.hausdorffMeasure"]},{"className":"MeasureTheory.Measure.IsAddHaarMeasure","name":"MeasureTheory.isAddHaarMeasure_hausdorffMeasure","typeNames":["MeasureTheory.Measure.hausdorffMeasure"]}],"name":"Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Measure.Hausdorff"}